Title: 14.1 Built-In Function and Operator Reference
Name: IS NOT NULL
Description: Tests whether a value is not NULL.

Press CTRL+C to copy mysql> SELECT 1 IS NOT NULL, 0 IS NOT NULL, NULL IS NOT NULL;
        -> 1, 1, 0
Examples:
mysql> SELECT 1 IS NOT NULL, 0 IS NOT NULL, NULL IS NOT NULL;
        -> 1, 1, 0
